%% Step-by-step traffic flow from a customer request to the response.
sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant U as Customer
    participant D as Cloud DNS
    participant L as Global HTTPS LB<br/>(Cloud Armor)
    participant M as MultiClusterIngress<br/>controller
    participant N as Cluster NEG<br/>(closest healthy)
    participant K as Ingress / Service
    participant P as Pod replica
    participant O as Observability<br/>(Logs, Trace, Metrics)

    U->>D: Resolve www.yourapp.com
    D-->>U: A record (anycast global IP)
    U->>L: TLS handshake + HTTPS request
    L->>L: SSL terminate, WAF inspect
    L->>M: Forward to backend service
    M->>N: Pick proximity / health-checked NEG
    N->>K: Container-native LB to ClusterIP svc
    K->>P: Round-robin to a Ready pod
    P->>P: Process request, emit structured logs + traces
    P-->>K: Response
    K-->>N: Response
    N-->>L: Response
    L-->>U: HTTPS response
    P-->>O: stdout JSON, OTel traces, Prom metrics
    L-->>O: LB request logs
